HEADWORD: Skeet
<hw>Skeet</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etymol.
uncertain.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A scoop with a long handle,
used to wash the sides of a vessel, and formerly to wet the sails or
deck.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

